==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solo
<hw>So"lo</hw> <pr>(s⟦omac⟧"l⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> E. <plw>Solos</plw> <pr>(s⟦omac⟧"l⟦omac⟧z)</pr>, It.
<plw>Soli</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[It., from L. <ets>solus</ets>
alone. See <er>Sole</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A
tune, air, strain, or a whole piece, played by a single person on an
instrument, or sung by a single voice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Solo
<hw>So"lo</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Music)</fld> <def>Performing, or
performed, alone; uncombined, except with subordinate parts, voices, or
instruments; not concerted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soloist</ent>⟦br⟧
